# Global Claude standards for Cursor

This file is a direct policy mirror of:

- `~/.claude/claude.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/behavior.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/tdd.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/logic-review.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/git-workflow.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/ci.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/code-standards.md`
- `~/.claude/standards/repo-structure.md`

If a repo-level `CLAUDE.md` or `AGENTS.md` is stricter, follow the stricter rule.

## Communication and execution

- Be concise and direct; lead with answer/action. _(source: `~/.claude/claude.md`, `standards/behavior.md`)_
- No filler text or emojis unless requested. _(source: `~/.claude/claude.md`)_
- Think before coding; read relevant code first. _(source: `standards/behavior.md`)_
- Prefer the smallest workable change. _(source: `standards/behavior.md`)_
- Keep diffs surgical; do not fix unrelated issues silently. _(source: `standards/behavior.md`)_
- Stay goal-driven; do not broaden scope without user confirmation. _(source: `standards/behavior.md`)_

## TDD and testing (required)

- TDD is required for feature and bug-fix work. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Use vertical RED -> GREEN cycles, one behavior at a time. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Tests must verify public behavior, not internal implementation details. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Mandatory coverage dimensions: boundary values, error paths, state transitions. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Test both branches for every guard/conditional. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`, `standards/logic-review.md`)_
- Maintain at least 90% line coverage as repository policy unless explicitly documented otherwise. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Add tests in the same commit as the corresponding code change. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`)_

## Logic review and correctness gates

- Run pre-commit logic review on changed code: conditionals, boundaries, scope/state, error paths, return/exit propagation, branch coverage, integration assumptions. _(source: `standards/logic-review.md`)_
- Fail-fast on upstream errors; do not continue on broken intermediate state. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`, `standards/logic-review.md`)_
- Do not suppress errors (`|| true`, `except: pass`, ignored errors) unless explicitly justified. _(source: `standards/tdd.md`, `standards/logic-review.md`)_
- For major changes (3+ functions, control-flow heavy, integration points), run deep review before PR. _(source: `standards/logic-review.md`)_

## Git workflow rules

- Do not commit implementation work directly to `master/main`; use feature branches and PRs. _(source: `standards/git-workflow.md`)_
- Exception: docs-only/memory-only updates may go direct when allowed by repo policy. _(source: `standards/git-workflow.md`)_
- Use PR monitoring until merged/failed, then clean local/remote stale branches. _(source: `standards/git-workflow.md`)_
- Run review gate before pushing feature branches; fix all critical findings first. _(source: `standards/git-workflow.md`)_
- After merge/direct master commit, run learning analysis and document durable learnings. _(source: `~/.claude/claude.md`, `standards/git-workflow.md`)_

## CI, hooks, and security baseline

- CI workflows should trigger on `pull_request` to `master`. _(source: `standards/ci.md`)_
- All actions should be Node 24 compatible; prefer `actions/checkout@v5`. _(source: `standards/ci.md`)_
- Build jobs must depend on tests. _(source: `standards/ci.md`)_
- Keep pre-commit and pre-push hooks present and active in every repo. _(source: `standards/ci.md`)_
- Pre-commit must include lint and local secret scan (`ggshield` when installed). _(source: `standards/ci.md`, `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- CI must include secret scanning (`gitleaks` + `.gitleaks.toml` allowlist). _(source: `standards/ci.md`, `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Add Snyk scan only for supported language repos; do not add to config-only repos. _(source: `standards/ci.md`)_

## Code standards baseline

- Keep shell/Ansible/Terraform changes idempotent. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`)_
- Shell scripts: `#!/usr/bin/env bash`, `[[ ... ]]`, `${VAR}`, `printf`, explicit error handling. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`)_
- Avoid `set -e` in general scripts (acceptable in git hooks). _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`)_
- In function bodies, use `|| return 1` (not `|| exit`). _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`, `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Propagate errors across full call chains. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`, `standards/tdd.md`)_
- Avoid over-engineering and speculative abstractions. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`, `standards/behavior.md`)_
- Prefer editing existing files over adding new files unless required. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`)_
- Comments should explain why, not what. _(source: `standards/code-standards.md`)_

## Repository structure baseline

- Every repo must include `README.md`. _(source: `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Every repo should have baseline `.gitignore` entries for macOS/Linux noise. _(source: `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Keep secret paths gitignored. _(source: `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Significant architectural decisions require ADRs. _(source: `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Maintain `docs/superpowers/` and `docs/cursor/` where the standards expect them. _(source: `standards/repo-structure.md`)_
- Keep docs (`README.md`, relevant `CLAUDE.md`) current when behavior/workflow changes. _(source: `~/.claude/claude.md`)_
